/*************************************************************************
   Code structure is like this:

   Vxxxxxx - is main file
             Here you call functions from other file to fit driver operation to your needs.


   Base - contains basic functions used like lock motor, mesure temperature...
          (Here add functions that will not depend on any other functions in other code files)

   Control - Contains main control algoritams like gravity compenstaion, position hold, velocity control...
             (Note*** Code in here is codependant on a lot of global variables that are in Globals.h and Motor_parameters.h)
             (Here add functions that affect control of the motor)

   Globals.h -  Contains bunch of global variables and pin definitions. Always try to keep this file as small as posibble and use
                small number of global variables.

   Magic - Basically a FOC algoritam that uses SVPWM lookup table to control the motor

   Motor_parameters.h - Contains bunch of global variables that have connections to the Control or motor protection

   Open_loop - Contains code for open loop control of BLDC motor. Also contains some direction checking functions


   SVPWM_table.h - Contains lookup tables for few different types of BLDC motors.
                   Tables can be generated by:
                   Matlab script:  https://github.com/PCrnjak/BLDC_SVPWM_lookup_table
                   Python script:  https://github.com/PCrnjak/Python_SVPWM_BLDC_Lookup_table


   Setup - Code that executes on startup of BLDC motor.
           There are different modes of startup and different modes of motor setup. Check Setup file for more info.


   Temperature_table.h - This file contains lookup table that maps termistor resistance values to actual temperature.
                         To generate one for your termistor use this code:
                         https://github.com/PCrnjak/Thermistor-table-generator-using-Steinhart-Hart-equation


  Communications - Contains code that receives commands from external MCU / PC and code that outputs data to external MCU / PC



 **************************************************************************/






